This paper deals with the convergence of the distribution over functions induced through a prior distribution over the parameters of a multi-layer perceptron (MLP) to a Gaussian process (GP). This topic is closely related to machine learning and neural networks, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the model on synthetic regression problems, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of MLPs in computer vision, which could relate to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
